#############################################################################################################################
#                                                   (CPC) - Custom Pattern Configuration
#############################################################################################################################
# ====================================================
# Format & Description of each configuration elements
# ====================================================
#
# CPC<<INDEX>>[#B/#KB]=<<MATCHING_URL_PATTERN>>~#~<<DESCRIPTION>>~!~HP[_REGEX]/US=<<QUERY_PARAM_KEY/URL_SEGMENT_INDEX>>~|~HP[_REGEX]/US=<<QUERY_PARAM_KEY/URL_SEGMENT_INDEX>>....
#
#             CPC<<INDEX>>              :   Custom Pattern Configuration Index 
#             [#B/#KB]                  :   Indicates that this pattern configuration is applied for BusinessTransTest or KeyBusinessTransTest, 
#                                              this is optional if not specified BusinessTransTest will be considered
#             <<MATCHING_URL_PATTERN>>  :   Apply the config only for matching URL patterns alone
#             <<DESCRIPTION>>           :   Description for the configuration
#             HP[_REGEX]                :   Indicates the value to be fetched dynamically from the Http Param, Regex is optional.
#                                              if Regex is present,it will be applied on Http param value part.
#             US                        :   Indicates the value to be fetched from URL Segment
#             <<QUERY_PARAM_KEY>>       :   Specific Key of the Query Param for which the value need to be captured
#             <<URL_SEGMENT_INDEX>>     :   Index position of the URL Segment - starts from 1, domain name and port will be ignored for URL Segment
#
#             NOTE :
#             =====
#                    1. HP/US related configurations can be specified more than once to capture more number of values. 
#                    2. Also the same query param can be specified more than once to capture different portions from the same value using regex.
#                    3. The user need to input Regex. pattern (Java API based) to be applied on the query param value part.
#
#
#             Example Configurations
#             ======================
#
#             CPC1#B=*/webstore/home.jsp~#~Home-Page~!~US=1~|~HP=type~|~HP=brand~|~HP=color~|~HP=size
#             CPC2#KB=*/addtocart*~#~AddToCart~!~HP=size~|~HP_some_xyz_some_abc_([a-zA-z]+)=brand~|~HP=color~|~HP_([a-zA-z]+)_=type~|~HP__([a-zA-z]+)=type~|~US=2
#             CPC3=*/removecart*~#~RemoveItem~!~US=3~|~HP=itemCode~|~HP=product~|~HP=type
#             CPC4=*~#~Catch_All~!~US=1~|~US=2~|~US=3
#
#############################################################################################################################




